description:
It was discovered that Python incorrectly stripped certain characters from
requests. A remote attacker could use this issue to perform CRLF injection.
(CVE-2019-18348)

It was discovered that Python incorrectly handled certain HTTP requests.
An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service.
(CVE-2020-8492)
title: Python vulnerabilities
summary: python2.7, python3.4, python3.5, python3.6, python3.7 vulnerabilities
action: In general, a standard system update will make all the necessary changes.
isummary: Several security issues were fixed in Python.
